lines.text: ALCOHOL, DRUG ABUSE, AND MENTAL HEALTH ADMINISTRATION
1/ Includes a proposed supplemental of $3, 637,000 for pay raises contained in the
2/ Includes $4,850 obligated in research and $1, 200 obligated in training.
The 25 percent increase in combined research funds for the three institutes com-
prising the Alcohol, Drug Abuse, and Mental Health Administration is attributable
primarily to preliminary recommendations of the President's Commission on Mental Health
to expand support for mental health research. The combined total requested for research
in 1979 is $202 million as against $162 million appropriated for 1978.
The combined total requested for training in the three institutes for 1979 is
$104 million compared with the $101 million appropriated in 1978. Of the total requested,
$21. 825 million is intended for research training, an increase of $2.9 million, or more
than 13 percent, over 1978. The $21.825 million requested for ADAMHA added to the
$147.973 million for NIH makes a total of $169.798 million for research training.
